==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strumpet
<hw>Strum"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>strumpet</ets>, <ets>strompet</ets>; cf. OF. <ets>stupe</ets>
debauchery, F. <ets>stupe</ets>, L. <ets>stuprare</ets>,
<ets>stupratum</ets>, to debauch, <ets>stuprum</ets> debauchery, Gael. &
Ir. <ets>striopach</ets> a prostitute.]</ety> <def>A prostitute; a
harlot.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strumpet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Strumpet
<hw>Strum"pet</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to a strumpet;
characteristic of a strumpet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Out on thy more than <qex>strumpet</qex> impudence.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strumpet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Strumpet
<hw>Strum"pet</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To debauch.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dishonor with the reputation of being a strumpet;
hence, to belie; to slander.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With his untrue reports, <qex>strumpet</qex> your fame.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strumstrum</ent>⟦br⟧
